{{For|the Church of England bishop|Bishop of Portsmouth (Anglican)}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} {{Use British English|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox Bishopric |border = catholic |font_color = black |bishopric = [[Portsmouth]] |coatofarms = Coat of arms of Philip Egan.svg |image = |incumbent = Bishop Philip Egan |province = [[Province of Southwark|Southwark]] |diocese = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Portsmouth|Portsmouth]] |cathedral = [[Cathedral of St John the Evangelist, Portsmouth]] |first_bishop = [[John Vertue]] |date = 1882 |website = }} The '''Bishop of Portsmouth''' is the [[Ordinary (officer)|Ordinary]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Portsmouth]] in the [[Province of Southwark]], England.<ref name=dprts>{{Catholic-hierarchy|diocese|dprts|Diocese of Portsmouth|14 June 2011}}</ref><ref name=GCatholicport4>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/port4.htm ''Diocese of Portsmouth''] at GCatholic.org.com. Retrieved on 14 June 2011.</ref>
The bishop's official residence is Bishop's House, Bishop Crispian Way, [[Portsmouth]], [[Hampshire]].<ref name=GCatholicport4/>
The current Bishop is [[Philip Egan]] who was ordained Bishop at St John's Cathedral, Portsmouth, on 24 September 2012, the Feast of [[Our Lady of Walsingham]].<ref name="bbc.co.uk">https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-hampshire-19691714</ref> Bishop Egan was previously the [[Vicar General]] for the [[Diocese of Shrewsbury]] and his appointment was announced by the Holy See on 11 July 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dioceseofshrewsbury.org/news/latest-news/pope-benedict-xvi-appoints-shrewsbury-vicar-general-as-bishop-of-portsmouth |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-07-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130310022828/http://www.dioceseofshrewsbury.org/news/latest-news/pope-benedict-xvi-appoints-shrewsbury-vicar-general-as-bishop-of-portsmouth |archivedate=10 March 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> The [[bishop emeritus]] is the Right Reverend [[Crispian Hollis]], the 7th Bishop of Portsmouth, who was appointed on 6 December 1988.<ref name=bhollis/> He reached retirement age (75) in November 2011, and retired as Bishop on 11 July 2012 upon his successor's appointment. Bishop Hollis acted as Apostolic Administrator of the Diocese of Portsmouth from 11 July 2012 until Bishop Egan's ordination on 24 September 2012.
==History== In 1688 the Portsmouth area came under the authority of the [[Vicar Apostolic of the London District]]. On the [[Universalis Ecclesiae|restoration of the Catholic hierarchy in England and Wales]] in 1850 Portsmouth became part of the [[Archdiocese of Southwark|Diocese of Southwark]]. On 19 May 1882 the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Portsmouth]] was created, and consists of the counties of [[Hampshire]] and [[Dorset]], together with [[Berkshire]] and [[Oxfordshire]] south of the [[River Thames]], plus the [[Isle of Wight]] and the [[Channel Islands]].<ref name=dprts/>
