{{Expand Spanish|Francisco del Castillo O.Merced.|date=December 2011}}
'''Francisco del Castillo O.Merced''' or '''Francisco del Castillo Andraca''' (1716–1770) was a [[Peru]]vian poet, writer and priest of the [[Order of the Blessed Virgin Mary of Mercy|Order of Mercy]].  Not to be confused with his namesake Francisco del Castillo SJ ( Jesuit of the seventeenth century), also from Lima.

Blind from birth, he was known as ''El Ciego de La Merced'' (The Blind Man from Mercy), and was a talented poet who combined wit and humor in his verses. [[Ricardo Palma]] would make a short biography of him (with some poems included), in his ''Peruvian Traditions''.

